clinical_notes: Patient presents with substernal chest pain, radiating to left arm. History of hypertension. ECG shows ST elevation. Troponin pending.
Temperature 101F, productive cough with yellow sputum. Chest clear on auscultation. SPO2 98% on room air.
BP 180/110 mmHg. No focal neurological deficit. Fundoscopy shows hypertensive retinopathy grade II.
Random blood sugar 280 mg/dL. Patient reports weight loss of 5 kg in 2 months. No ketones in urine.
